    What is green energy?
    </mj-text>
       
       <mj-image
       src="https://i.postimg.cc/J43HJrMt/house.png"
       alt="solar-panel-house"
       width="400px"
       >
       </mj-image>

       <mj-text 
       line-height="25px"
       align="center"
       color="#ffffff"
       font-size="20px"
       padding-bottom="30px">
       
       Green power is a subset of renewable energy. It represents those
        renewable energy resources and technologies that provide the 
        greatest environmental benefit. Within the U.S. voluntary market,
         green power is defined as electricity produced from solar, wind, 
         geothermal, biogas, eligible biomass, and low-impact small 
         hydroelectric sources.
       </mj-text>
    </mj-column>
